<%# locals: (chip:, emphasis: false) %>
<%# MiClassrooms Phase 4 Task 4 (Brief §5.3): one characteristic chip — an
    icon + visible-text badge. When the characteristic has a long description it
    is wrapped in UI::TooltipComponent as a SUPPLEMENTARY hint (WCAG 1.4.13:
    hoverable, keyboard-focusable, Escape-dismissible) — the badge carries the
    visible label, so the tooltip only adds detail and never gates the
    accessible name. The badge is a plain, non-interactive <span>, so the
    tooltip's focusable wrapper is not a nested-interactive violation.

    2026-07-14: `emphasis: true` promotes the chip to the AAA-proven
    [:soft, :primary] cell for the always-visible results-card strip; the quiet
    [:outline, :neutral] default is what the room page AND the card's <details>
    remainder use. NOTE: [:soft, :neutral] is NOT an AAA-proven Badge cell (it
    raises), which is why emphasis rides :primary. %>
<% badge = capture do %>
  <%= ui :badge, variant: (emphasis ? :soft : :outline), tone: (emphasis ? :primary : :neutral) do %>
    <%= icon(chip.icon_name, size: :xs) %>
    <%= chip.label %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>

<% if chip.description.present? %>
  <%= render(UI::TooltipComponent.new(text: chip.description)) { badge } %>
<% else %>
  <%= badge %>
<% end %>
